The GSMA has named the Sony Xperia XZ Premium the best new smartphone at the annual Global Mobile Awards. Sony’s smartphone won the award for “Best New Smartphone or Connected Mobile Device at MWC 2017.” The Xperia XZ Premium features Sony Motion Eye camera technology, allowing it to record at 960fps and display recorded videos in super slow motion. The device sports a 4K HDR display and a Qualcomm Snapdragon 835 processor. “Xperia XZ Premium is our most technologically-capable smartphone ever. We’re honoured by this recognition,” said Sony Mobile CEO Hiroki Totoki.